{{wikt|bannock|Bannock}} '''Bannock''' may mean:
* [[Bannock (food)]], a kind of bread, usually prepared by pan-frying * [[Bannock people]], a Native American people of what is now southeastern Oregon and western Idaho * [[Bannock County, Idaho]] * [[Bannock, Ohio]] * [[Bannock Pass]], between Idaho and Montana * [[Russell Bannock]] (born 1919), Canadian World War II flying ace and test pilot
== See also == *[[Bannack, Montana]], town named after the tribe, today a ghost town
